  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, we knew that during that time Hungarians were rewarded by Hitler for some of the damages which the country suffered after World War I.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of the territories which were taken away from Hungary after losing the First World War were returned to Hungary, mostly territories which had major Hungarian populations, which were part of Czechoslovakia and Romania and Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in those territories, there was a very large Jewish population as well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And those Jewish population which was returned to Hungary were in some way not the assimilated Jews, which the Hungarians-- many of the Hungarians Jews wanted to be.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I say assimilated in appearance and in culture.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were more the very traditional, old fashioned, shtetl Jews, the-- the town people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many of the Hungarian Gentile population found them very weird.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and many of the Hungarian Jewish population who was different, because they were this so-called assimilated Jews, and I was one of those of my family, we were-- even so if we were very religious, but we were trying to be as much Hungarian and as any other Hungarian of Gentile background and origin.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we tried to fit in and be Hungarians more than anybody else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But this portions of the country which returned to Hungary by this-- by this returning of the territories which were taken away at World War I, gave an influx of Jews who were-- then lost their homes because of the changing of who is the ruler and moved into the Hungarian portion of it.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And many of them wanted to seek positions and jobs and then-- and livelihood in bigger cities and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
